title: Grateful Dead Live at Musikhalle on 1972-04-29
description:
Set 1

Playin' In The Band, Sugaree, Mr. Charlie, Black Throated Wind, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Big Boss Man, Jack Straw, Loser, Chinatown Shuffle, Me & My Uncle, Big Railroad Blues, Good Lovin', Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, He's Gone, Next Time You See Me, Dark Star-> Sugar Magnolia-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks)-> Who Do You Love, E: One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band*

Second Encore

reviews.review_text:
One of the best AUD's 1972 ! Hi GD folks,   Like many of you I had the 2nd gen copy of this source; this is a signifiant upgrade.  I think Europe 72 was the best tour in the GD's history.  It is impossible to say what is the best show from that tour, but this is nice well played concert.  

If I recall from the other source, the taper had the microphones from the balcony rail which would explain the low crowd cheer ambience and excellent sound of the hall.  It's really nice to hear that 72 sound of the PA, they really had a great sound.  I actually prefer the 72 PA sound to 73, and the wall of sound in 74.  The only other AUD sources that rival this recording are the 72 shows that Bear recorded from the soundboard.  

Kudos to our crack equipment team for the transfer - I'll just pose the inevitable question, "what happened to the second encore of Uncle John's Band"?  Anyway, if you like AUD source; this one is a real treat,  and a diamond in the rough.

Great Experience I'm really excited to have found this recording. I was present at this show, and it was one of the greatest shows I've ever been to. They started at 8pm and played well beyond midnight. In the end the Musikhalle staff turned off the power because they wanted to go home. Otherwise they would have probably played throughout the night. I also saw them in later years in Munich and in Frankfurt, but the Hamburg show was the best ever.
